. 
<taxonomicName LSID="0E4B8EA4-6C39-59A5-A445-7F93D29BA06A" authority="Svent., Addit. Fl. Canar. 1: 46. 1960. (Sventenius 1960: 46)." authorityName="Svent., Addit. Fl. Canar. 1: 46. 1960. (Sventenius" authorityYear="1960" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lopezsocasii" order="Solanales" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lopezsocasii">Convolvulus lopezsocasii Svent., Addit. Fl. Canar. 1: 46. 1960. (Sventenius 1960: 46).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="109" pageNumber="110" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
CANARY ISLANDS, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Lopezsocas</emphasis>
s.n. (probable holotype ORT-22418- but collection date does not correspond exactly).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="109" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brouss. ex Link, Phys. Beschr. Canar. Ins. 145. 1828 [1825]. (Buch" authorityYear="1828" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus volubilis" order="Solanales" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="volubilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Convolvulus volubilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but leaves 3-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
3-4.2 cm, ovate-elliptic, obtuse, entire, base rounded to subcordate, dark green, glabrous. Flowers 1-6 in axillary pedunculate cymes; peduncles 1.5-3.5 cm, bracteoles 5-12 mm, filiform, somewhat caducous; pedicels 10-18 mm, sepals 9-12 mm, oblong-obovate with a distinct triangular apiculate apex, subglabrous; corolla 1.6-2 cm, pink, unlobed, midpetaline bands darker; ovary c. 3 mm long, conical, thinly pilose; style glabrous, divided c. 4 mm above base. Capsule and seeds not seen. [
<bibRefCitation author="Bramwell, D" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Egypt" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" refId="B60" refString="Bramwell, D, Bramwell, Z, 2001. Wild flowers of the Canary Islands (2nd ed.). Rueda, Madrid, 1-437." title="Wild flowers of the Canary Islands (2 nd ed.). Rueda, Madrid, 1 - 437." year="2001">Bramwell and Bramwell 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 264-265 (photo)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="109" pageNumber="110" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
Endemic to Lanzarote in the Canary Islands at 400-600 m (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Murray</emphasis>
s.n. [16/5/1902], 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Stearn</emphasis>
1124-cultivated on Gran Canaria).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
